This paper involves data mining and analysis of metadata available through the Wikidata database, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL). The study also involves the use of cultural clusters to analyze gender inequality, which could fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also touches upon demographics and the coverage of females and other genders in reference works, which could fall under social computing (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
